tensive exercise section.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aEuropean literaturexRenaissance, 1450-1600. 0aLITERARY CRITICISMxEuropeanxFrench. 0aRomance languages. 0aRomance literaturexHistory and criticism. 4aEinführung. 4aLinguistik. 4aRomanistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aLinguistics.  aMethodology.  aRomance Studies.1 aPöll, Bernhard, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRainer, Franz, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK 2013z9783110317237oZDB-23-DSP0 cprintz978311031013940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311031069640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110310696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110310696/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-DLSc2000d2014  aZDB-23-DSPb2013